FlexCards Versioning and Cloning

FlexCards supports versioning and cloning. You can create an identical copy of a FlexCard based on how you want to use the new version.

To update a FlexCard already published, and elsewhere, create a new **version**.

To make slight modifications to an existing FlexCard to test behavior and layout, create a new **version**.

To create a new FlexCard but copy over layout, settings, or both, **clone** the current one.

FlexCards supports versioning. Create a new version when you want to make slight modifications to a FlexCard already published. 
FlexCards Cloning
FlexCards supports cloning. You can create a new FlexCard by cloning a current one to update the Author and/or Name, and copy over layout and/or settings.
Follow requirements when naming FlexCards and FlexCard elements to prevent errors when working with the FlexCard Designer and importing FlexCards as datapacks.
